Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.68,0:03:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当你的世界在包装下 随身携带\NWhen your world in a bag by your side{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.81,0:03:40.99,顶部,,0,0,0,,当天早些时候...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.80,0:04:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}现在是早上7点 你好 纽约\NIt's 7AM. Good Moring, New York.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}欢迎今早与Potsy和Andy的"第二小时"相会\NAnd welcome to THE SECOND HOUR of Posty and Andy in the morning.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.96,0:04:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Potsy 你有听说过一只\NHey Potsy, did you read about a dog in{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.11,0:04:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在一家韩国餐馆的狗的故事吗?\Nthe Korean restaurant thing?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.82,0:04:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我当然听说过 你听说过吗 Katie?\NOh I certainly did. Did you hear about that, Katie?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.88,0:05:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,潜力新人歌手 让我听听看都有些什么人\NFresh prospects, Let's hear it, what do you got for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不\NNo No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.90,0:05:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,下一个让谁来点亮这旅程?\NWho's next on this delightful journey?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.82,0:05:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不 不 天 不行!完全不行!\NNo,no,no,no man! You can't! No! You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这都什么破玩意儿\NIt's shit! It’s shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.01,0:05:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,滚出我的车\NGet fucking out of my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.94,0:05:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,给我随便来点什么 一首歌 一点希望 什么都可以\NGive me anything, a song, a hope anything I can work with...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.23,0:05:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我要求不高\NI'm not asking for much...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这还行 还可以\NThat's something, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.63,0:05:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不再唱了的话\NUntil you started to sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.80,0:06:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈在哪?\NWhere's mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.96,0:06:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我女儿在哪呢?\NWhere's my daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.86,0:06:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么意思?\NWhat do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.95,0:06:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你妈今天要截稿 她让我今天来照顾你\NYour mom has a deadline, she asked me to watch you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.35,0:06:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,上车吧\NLet's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.27,0:06:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 你现在想要去哪?自然历史博物馆吗?\NSo where do you want to go? The Museum of Natural History?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.96,0:06:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,或者是去公园吃个冰淇淋还是怎样?\NYou want to go to the park and get some ice cream, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.03,0:06:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我为什么要干那些?我又不是小孩子\NWhy would I want to do that? I'm not a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,车上什么味道?\NWhat's that smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.22,0:07:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 是汽油味 我在加满油的时候\NOh that's gasoline. I was filling up the car with gasoline
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.90,0:07:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我洒了点在我裤子上\Nand I spilled a little on my pant leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.11,0:07:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,并不是酒\NThat isn't alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.60,0:07:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我感觉我好像要在这开个会\NI think I've got a meeting here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.06,0:07:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你要在这里等还是要一起进去?\NYou want to wait here or you want to come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.78,0:07:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你感觉你有个会?你到底有没有?\NYou think you have a meeting? Do you or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.37,0:07:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,去看看呗\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.67,0:07:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,看 这很不错吧\NSee, this is fun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.99,0:07:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们第一次来这附近的时候还是在92年\NWhen we came into this neighborhood in 92.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.95,0:07:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,那时这里一个人也没有 就像一个战区\NThere was nobody here, it was like a war-zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.92,0:07:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,都是妓女啊 盗贼啊 现在高雅多了\NHookers. Crack. Now it's totally gentrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.80,0:07:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道的 老爸\NI know, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.67,0:07:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我来过的 - 那好 现在我们要上去了 尽量保持安静\N- I've had the tour. - Okay we're going to go up there. Just be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我认为这是公司赚取利润的一个好方法\NI think it's a great way to generate revenue for the company.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.32,0:07:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你来啦 交通很糟糕么? - 没有 交通很通畅啊 我只是路过一下\N- Hey.Hmm,was there bad traffic? - No,traffic was actually pretty good. I was just passing by.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.20,0:08:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,我们刚结束音频评论会\NWe were just hmm...closing up about the audio commentary piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.03,0:08:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,恩 太糟糕了\NYeah, shit idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.88,0:08:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个糟糕的想法 怎么讨论也是糟糕的\NIt was a shit idea then, Still a shit idea. It didn't age well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.67,0:08:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们感谢你的坦率\NWe appreciate your candor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.61,0:08:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,但是今天我们涌现了很多不同的意见\NBut we had a different view of it here though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.45,0:08:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 现在大多数的音乐家是\NI mean. Musicians for the most part are pretty much...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.83,0:08:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,十几岁没什么话好说的青少年\NMonosyllabic teenagers who really don't have much to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.75,0:08:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,这想法不错吧\Nand that's the good one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.07,0:08:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这样的话我们还在这里做什么?\NSo what are we doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.86,0:08:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,音乐行业好着呢 会一直好下去的\NThe music industry is fine. It's always gonna be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.84,0:08:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在很稳定\NWe always have been fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,也许孩子们说的是对的 也许音乐真的应该免费\NMaybe the kids are right. Maybe music should be free anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.86,0:08:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,从唱片公司老板听到这番话可真可怕\NThat's an alarming thing to hear the head of a record company say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.55,0:08:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,怕什么?真相么?\NWhat? The truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.68,0:08:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 Karen我们回聊感谢你的到来\NWell,hmm...Thanks so much, Karen. Let's talk more. We really appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.96,0:08:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 当然\NYeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.72,0:08:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴认识你\NGreat meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.54,0:08:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴大家都能理解这个问题\NI'm glad we got it all figured out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}乐队评论他们自己音乐的音轨\NThe band doing audio commentary on their own music.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.87,0:08:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是唯一套路 Saul 你是知道的\NIt's so fucking lame, Saul, you know it!{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.98,0:09:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果是十年前的话 你肯定会看不起那些主意的\N10 years ago, man, you would have shit on that idea.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.21,0:09:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,这也是一些东西 一些想法\NIt's something, it's an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.15,0:09:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,这些想法说不定能打开思路 这都是些东西\NIt's something that helps keep the lights on. It's something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.35,0:09:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要创造力 而不是什么噱头 这就是我们\NWe need vision, not gimmicks.That's us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我一直在跟你做 Mulligan先生\NI've been following you, Mr.Mulligan
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.92,0:09:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,寻找各种有潜力的人\NDown a track on every long shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.03,0:09:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,然后带到这里 但在过去的5年里\NYou've been bringing in here the last five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.03,0:09:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,他们之中有人红了么?\NAnd which one of them has come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.07,0:09:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,有么?\NWhich one?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.98,0:09:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Dan Dan.\NDan Dan
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.61,0:09:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,再见 Saul\NSee you later, brother Saul.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.07,0:09:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Dan.\NDan
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要谈谈\NWe need to talk, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.70,0:09:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}回来 你别走 你不能这么做\NCome back here. Don't you walk away from me.You can't do this shit, man.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.92,0:09:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能这么做\NYou can't pull this shit, dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.75,0:09:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你不能这样对我\NYou can't pull this shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.59,0:09:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,不要这样\NDon't do this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.13,0:09:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我就要这么做\NI'm going to do it right fucking here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 那我就这么做了\NAll right, then let's do it then!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.83,0:09:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他们知道 这些人知道\NBecause they know. These people know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.86,0:10:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他们能够在这上班\Nthat they are sitting behind those desks
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.83,0:10:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为我建立了一个独立的唱片公司\Nis because I started an independent record label.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.92,0:10:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,在那家酒吧开始的 Saul\NAbove that bar, Saul.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.16,0:10:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经改变了当时做事的方式\NAnd we changed the way things are going to be done, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.45,0:10:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,培育然后培养\NNurture and foster.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.65,0:10:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都变了 时代变了\NThings change. Times change.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.78,0:10:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,人们必须做出改变 Dan\NPeople gotta change with them, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.02,0:10:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,这样已经没用了\NIt's not working.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.93,0:10:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你得走了\NYou gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.15,0:10:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我可没时间浪费在这\NI don't have time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.38,0:10:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我还有自己的事要处理 好吗?\NI've got my own shit going on, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.86,0:10:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我要去拿我的客户名单了\NI'm taking my client list.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.73,0:10:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我要走了 我他妈的这就走\NI'm out of here, man. I am fucking out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你在说什么 他们已经和我们签署了合同\NWhat are you talking about? They signed to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.76,0:10:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,不要打扰她 别打扰她\NDon't bother her. Don't bother her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.86,0:10:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,她可不会什么事都替你做\NThat's not Jerry McGuire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.27,0:10:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧 爸爸\NDad, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.37,0:10:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,那我要带走我的画 就这么决定了 我要带走我的画\NI'm taking my art then. That's it. I'm taking the art.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的画 我花的钱 是我买的 是我选的\NIt's my art. I paid for it. I bought it. I picked it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.69,0:10:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- 没问题 没问题 我拿着呢 - 你想去哪?\N- I got this. I got it. I got it. - Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.87,0:11:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 先放这里\NOkay. Leave it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.90,0:11:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我会回来拿的 这是我的\NI'm coming back for that.It's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.49,0:11:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的东西都是我的\NAll of that is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.33,0:11:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,走吧 宝贝\NCome on, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.78,0:11:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你想要再喝一杯吗?\NYou want another one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.08,0:11:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,恩 我想 但我不会要的 不行 我不能\NAh, I do but I won't. I mustn't. I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.88,0:11:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他怎么能炒掉我 是我建立了那个公司诶!\NHow could he fire me when I set the whole fucking thing up?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,是你么?\NDid you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.29,0:11:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么一点也不了解你爸我\NDon't you know anything about your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.43,0:11:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我知道\NYeah I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.68,0:11:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,妈妈经常说的\NI know what mom says.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.87,0:11:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你妈妈说什么?\NWhat does mom say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.99,0:11:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,她说你只是个悲惨的失败者\NShe says you're a pathetic loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.19,0:11:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,她说得真亲切\NShe says that affectionately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.99,0:11:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你呢?\NWhat about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.13,0:11:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么觉得?\NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我不怎么了解你\NI don't really know you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.37,0:11:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道两年的时间对一个十几岁的孩子来说是很长的\NYou know two years is a long time in the life of a teenager.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.19,0:11:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你这说话方式哪学的?\NWhere did you learn to talk like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.38,0:11:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我的心理医生\NMy psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.73,0:12:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,心理医生?你有心理医生?\NPsychiatrist? You have a psychiatrist now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.21,0:12:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 妈妈觉得这挺好的\NI do. Mom thought it'd be a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我有点行为怪异\NI was acting strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.57,0:12:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你没什么奇怪的 你只是个15岁的青少年\NThere's nothing strange about you.You're 15 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.21,0:12:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,你并不需要什么心理医生\NYou don't need a fucking psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.86,0:12:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,相信我 我知道的 我比任何人都了解你\NBelieve me, I know. I know you better than anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.74,0:12:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,恩 当然了 爸爸\NYeah, you sure do, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.47,0:12:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你说我几岁来着?\NHow old did you say I was?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.44,0:12:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚说15岁?\NDid I say you were 15?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.46,0:12:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我是指 是指14岁\NI meant you were 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.40,0:12:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚说15吗?\NDid I say 15?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.44,0:12:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你有还酒的钱么?\NYou got money to pay for these beers?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.07,0:12:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个孩子 我哪来的钱?\NI'm a kid. I don't have any money on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.19,0:12:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你的零花钱呢?\NWhat happened to your pocket money?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.51,0:12:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我拿去买避孕套了\NWell, I spent that on condoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.69,0:12:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,什么?不 不 不 不 不\NWhat? No, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,信息量太大了\NToo much information.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.80,0:12:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你准备好了吗?干嘛?\NYou ready?For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.88,0:13:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- 有趣的是吧 是吧?不要笑 - 恩 是挺有趣的 老爸\NThat was fun, right? Don't smile.It was fun, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.77,0:13:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 好久没这么开心了\NYeah. You had a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.98,0:13:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你还小的时候我们都没这样过 真是有趣\NWe haven't run like that since we were little. That was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.90,0:13:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他是你爸么?\NIs he your daddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.17,0:13:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴你在这里因为我正准备上车...\NI'm glad you're here because I was just going to the car...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.53,0:13:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你还好吗?我很好\NAre you okay?I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.88,0:13:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起 是我的错 祝你有个愉快的一天\NI'm sorry, my bad. Have a great day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.24,0:13:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我还是能够打败他的 会让他出丑的\NI could have taken that guy. He still had to make a scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.92,0:13:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,帮我件事 好吗?不要告诉妈妈我今天被炒了 听着\NDo me a favor, all right? Don't tell your mom I lost my job today.Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,感谢你让我度过了极其平常的一天\NThanks for a really normal day, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.58,0:13:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,什么?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.16,0:13:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,大家好啊\NHello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.66,0:13:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嗨\N- Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.61,0:13:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,工作怎样?\NHow's work?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,还行\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.32,0:14:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你饿了吧\NYou look hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.81,0:14:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}老师真的很担心她\NHer teachers are really worried about her.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.34,0:14:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没有女孩子喜欢她 她很难接近\NNo girls like her at school. She is distant.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.74,0:14:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}想跟她玩的\NAnd the only people who want to hang out with her{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.08,0:14:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,都是那些想和她睡的大男孩\Nare older boys who want to fuck her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.23,0:14:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 是这样吗?我并不感到惊讶\NOh really? And you find that a big surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.40,0:14:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你让她穿着就像\NYou let her walk out of the house looking like...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.92,0:14:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jodie Foster在"出租车司机"里一样走出家门?\Nlike Jodie Foster from "Taxi Driver"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.23,0:14:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,她有自己想要的穿衣方式\NShe dresses the way she wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.09,0:14:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- 而且如果女儿穿成那样只是想要一件事 - 当皮条客?\N- And any daughter who dresses like that only wants one thing. - A pimp?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.79,0:14:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,不 Dan 想想吧\NNo, Dan. Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.89,0:14:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这都是瞎扯!她需要些教育 天啊\NThat is fucking bullshit.She needs some guidance for fucking sake.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.26,0:14:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你走进来就跟个小丑似的\NYou walks in here like a fucking clown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.87,0:14:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,还对我教育孩子指手画脚\NYou tell me how to raise my kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.86,0:14:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你只不过是一个月来接孩子出去一次\NThe kid that you pick up once a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.00,0:14:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,就说得你很有良心似的\NAnd decide you have a fucking conscience about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.11,0:14:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?你离开这里30秒后\NYou know what? Thirty seconds after you're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.19,0:14:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就完全忘记了你曾经在这里\NWe'll have totally forgotten you were ever here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.09,0:15:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我以为我没希望了\NI thought there was no hope.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.02,0:15:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我以为已经没有答案了\NI thought there were no answers.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.13,0:15:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是后来我遇见了上帝\NAnd then I found God.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.28,0:16:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他也许不会一直在我们身边\NGod may not always be on our time.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.81,0:16:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但他总会准时到来\NBut he's on time.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.83,0:16:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们永远不会孤单\NWe're never alone.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.90,0:16:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,先生?去吧 跟上帝谈谈吧\NSir? Go, have a talk with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.83,0:16:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 很好\NRight, Man. OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.87,0:16:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我会跟他谈谈的 好么?\NI'm gonna have a little talk with God, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他不回答呢?\NWhat if he doesn't answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.35,0:16:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,请注意由于Jay Street站的出现故障\NAttention. Due to a signal malfunction at Jay Street
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.69,0:16:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,下一班列车将在20分钟后抵达\Nthe next uptown train will arrive in 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.58,0:16:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,快来一杯波旁酒\NGive me a bourbon. Hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.26,0:16:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你想要哪种?\NWhat kind of bourbon you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.73,0:17:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,随便\NI don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.90,0:17:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我在想能不能让她上来唱首歌\Nand I was wondering if it'd be okay if she sang a song.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.77,0:17:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}好吗?可以吗?Gretta 能请你上来吗?\NIs that okay? Yeah? Gretta, would you come up here please?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.92,0:17:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}嗨 这是一首新歌 还不是很完美\NSo this is a new song so it might be kind of rough.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.70,0:17:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}献给城市中所有寂寞的人们\NIt's for anyone who's ever been alone in the city.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你发现自己在地铁里\NSo you find yourself at this subway{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.90,0:17:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当你的世界在包装下 随身携带\NWhen your world in a bag by your side{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.88,0:17:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一切似乎看起来很完美\NAnd all at once it seemed like a good way{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.86,0:17:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你意识到这就是你生命的终结\NYou realized its the end of your life{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.74,0:18:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}意义也就如此\NFor what it's worth{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}火车在轨道上奔驰而来\NHere comes the train upon the track{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.78,0:18:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}带走伤痛只剩下一片黑\NAnd there goes the pain it cuts to black{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.91,0:18:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最后的行动你准备好了吗?\NAre you ready for the last act?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.79,0:18:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}踏上永不回头的征程\NTo take a step you can't take back{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.81,0:18:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}承受所有你能承受的逆境\NTake in all the punches you could take {\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.76,0:18:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}把一切放进心里\NTook 'em all right on your chest{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.45,0:18:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}此刻 无数次的回头打破这一切\NNow the countless back is breaking{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.06,0:18:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}再一次 再一次\NAgain, again{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.33,0:19:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}意义也就如此\NFor what it's worth{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.90,0:19:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}火车在轨道上奔驰而来\NHere comes the train upon the track{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.81,0:19:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}带走伤痛\NAnd there goes the pain{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.74,0:19:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只剩下一片黑\Nit cuts to black{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.78,0:19:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最后的行动你准备好了吗\NAre you ready for the last act?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.91,0:19:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}踏上\NTo take a step{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.86,0:19:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}永不回头的征程\Nyou can't take back{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.69,0:19:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她爱你吗?\NDid she love you? {\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.92,0:19:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她带给你伤痛吗?\NDid she take you down?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.88,0:19:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在亲吻你的王冠时\NWas she on her knees{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.90,0:19:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她有没有双膝跪地?\Nwhen she kissed your crown?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.91,0:19:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}告诉我你所知道的\NTell me what you found{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.58,0:20:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}大雨不期而至 抓紧你的帽子\NHere comes the rain, so hold your hat{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.78,0:20:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不要祈祷上帝 因为他不会跟你对讲\NAnd don't pray to God, cause He won't talk back{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.91,0:20:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}最后的行动你准备好了吗?\NAre you ready for the last act?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.75,0:20:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}踏上永不回头的征程\NTo take a step you can't take back{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.61,0:20:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不回头 不回头\NBack, back{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.65,0:20:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你不会回头\NYou can't take back{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.73,0:20:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不回头 不回头\NBack, back{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.85,0:20:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你发现自己在地铁里\NSo you find yourself at this subway{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.76,0:20:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当你的世界在包装下 随身携带\Nwith your world in a bag by your side{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.10,0:20:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我要加入 - 什么?\N- I'm in. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.75,0:21:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我想帮你出唱片 我想当你的制作人\NI want to make records with you，I want to produce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要签你 我们注定要一起合作\NI want to sign you. We're meant to work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.83,0:21:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起 你没看见他们的反应么?\NSorry, didn't you just see what happened up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.53,0:21:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,看见了啊 那又怎样 你觉得不好么?\NYeah, what? Are you feeling sorry for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.01,0:21:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我喜欢我的音乐 反正他们也不懂是吧?\NNo, I like my music. I mean who cares if they don't get it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.96,0:21:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你只需要稍微改善一下你的表演形式\NYou just need to work on your performance a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.22,0:21:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是表演家 我只是偶尔写点歌\NI'm not a performer. I just write songs from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.56,0:21:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,其他歌也跟这首一样好么?\NAnd are those songs as good as that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.47,0:21:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是个制作人?\NAre you really an A and R man?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.49,0:21:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但你看起来就像个无家可归的人\NYou just look more like a homeless man.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.46,0:21:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是出来庆祝一下\NI've been out celebrating all week.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.64,0:21:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我刚刚签了一个新乐队 我们感到非常兴奋\NAnd I just signed a band and we got carried away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.12,0:21:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你刚才唱的这首歌\NThat's some song you've got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.75,0:21:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我敢保证一定会大热 你又这么漂亮\NI promise you it could be a big hit. Plus you're beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.40,0:21:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,等等 这跟长相又有什么关系?\NSorry, what does beauty got to do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.22,0:21:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 你还挺精明的是吧?\NJesus, you’re tricky aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.92,0:21:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我是觉得是音乐是用耳朵来听的 而不是用眼睛看\NNo, I actually just think that music is about ears not eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.26,0:21:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我不是从灰狗巴士上走下来的Judy Garland\NAnd I'm not Judy Garland just off a Greyhound bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.49,0:21:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,想要寻找新开始 不过说真的 还是谢谢你\Nlooking for stardom, but really, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.53,0:21:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好吧 再见 - 再见\N- Okay, bye. - Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.59,0:22:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所以 在你走之前\NSo before you go{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.98,0:22:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}享受我的表演\NEnjoy my show{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.58,0:22:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好吧 其实事实是这样的 我想签你我也做不到 好吗? - 好吧\N- OK, here's the truth. I couldn't have signed you if I wanted to, alright? - OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.49,0:22:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我今晚来着并不是想要签谁\NI didn't come from a signing tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.46,0:22:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经七年没跟人签过合同了\NI haven't signed anybody in seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.40,0:22:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我的公司已经对我完全失去信心了\NMy label has completely lost all faith in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.54,0:22:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那你为什么还给我你的名片?\NSo why did you give me your card?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.23,0:22:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,职业病罢了 我看起来像无家可归的人么 事实上是可以这么说\NForce of habit.If I look homeless it's because I practically am.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.53,0:22:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我离开家大约有一年了\NI left my home about a year or so ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.50,0:22:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我住在一个地毯皱巴巴的糟糕的公寓里\NI'm sleeping on a shitty mattress in some shitty apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.89,0:22:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚来这也不是来庆祝的\NAnd I wasn't celebrating tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.91,0:22:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我醉醺醺地站在铁轨旁 准备自杀\NI was drinking my ass off standing on a subway platform ready to kill myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.78,0:22:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,然后 我听见了你的歌\NAnd then I heard your song.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.96,0:22:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- 想要喝杯酒吗? - 好啊 - 走\N- Want to get a beer? - Sure. - Yeah, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.99,0:22:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dan Mulligan 生于1966年\NDan Mulligan. Born 1966
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.96,0:22:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,在海岛唱片公司工作两年\NHeaded A&R department at Island Records for two years
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.94,0:22:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,之后与哈佛友人Saul Byron\NLeft to co-found indie label Distressed Records
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.77,0:22:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,共同创立独立音乐厂牌"\Nwith Harvard classmate, Saul Byron."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.17,0:22:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 你有自己的厂牌?\NSo, you own Distressed Records?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.84,0:22:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,但因为感情问题 我卖出了我所有的股权\NI sold all my interest due to emotional difficulties.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.53,0:23:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,什么感情问题?\NWhat emotional difficulties?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.14,0:23:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我太情绪化了而已 继续读下去\NI was too emotional. Read on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.03,0:23:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"90年代初 纽约开始流行起hip-pop音乐\N"Very active on the hip-hop scene in New York in the early 90s
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.84,0:23:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,他挖掘了\Nthe pair were responsible for discovering
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.40,0:23:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,许多创作型的歌手并获得两项格莱美奖\Nnumerous break-through artists on two Grammys as producer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.01,0:23:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,现与他的女儿以及妻子--音乐记者Miriam Hart一起居住在纽约\NLives in New York with wife--music journalist Miriam Hart, and their daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.55,0:23:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,格莱美奖是怎么回事?\NWhat happened to the Grammys?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.30,0:23:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我把奖杯都当掉了\NI pawned them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.46,0:23:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你当掉?赚了多少?\NYou pawned them? How much did you get for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.28,0:23:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,两个奖杯共一百二十五美元\NA hundred and twenty five for the both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.43,0:23:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,导致我前几个月一直醉着酒\NWhich got me wasted one weekend a couple months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.89,0:23:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,听我的歌时你也是醉着的吗?\NWere you drunk when you heard my song?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.03,0:23:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,当然 这样才能创造奇迹\NAbsolutely, babe. That's when the magic happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.28,0:23:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么奇迹? - 我从你的歌里听出一些东西\N- What magic? - I hear things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.85,0:23:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,一些东西?\NYou hear things?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.31,0:23:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,编曲 也许得醉了才能听的出来\NArrangements. Maybe need to be drunk for that sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.81,0:23:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,那你真是太醉了\NYou must have been drunk tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.47,0:23:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,因为在哪都能听到些东西\Nbecause nobody else heard anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.95,0:23:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,不 你的歌真的很棒 就是你的感觉\NNo, your song's good. It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.86,0:23:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,站在那里就像个假小子\NStanding up there like a tomboy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.36,0:23:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,无意冒犯\NI don’t mean to be offensive...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.49,0:23:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但你不觉得这样看着有点消极? - 真的吗?\N- But don't you think that looks a little pass? - Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.08,0:23:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,说真的 我们能把你包装好\NSeriously. We get you a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.82,0:23:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,再配上超品质的音乐视频 你一定能大热\NAnd a killer video. And you'll go straight to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.20,0:24:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我想到诺拉 琼斯 各种创作型歌手...\NI’m thinking Nora Jones. Singer songwriter thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.55,0:24:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,钢琴乐队还有羊毛衫合唱团\Nand The Piano or The Cardigans.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.53,0:24:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,想想他们刚到美国的样子吧 或者说像黛博拉 哈瑞一样\NBack in the day when they first came to America. Maybe even Deborah Harry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.86,0:24:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,给你后面配上乐队 怎么了?你觉得这很好笑?\NA male band behind you，What? You find that amusing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.03,0:24:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,不 对不起 但好像有什么不对劲\NNo, I'm sorry. Something went down the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.06,0:24:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你在把我跟羊毛衫合唱团还有诺拉 琼斯放在一个段位上?\NNo, you were saying? Me with a Cardigan on? Nora Jones?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.72,0:24:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,那你觉得自己是什么水平?\NBabe, what the fuck do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.75,0:24:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么?你以为你就拿着一把吉他站在舞台上\NWhat? You gonna stand up on a stage with a beat-up guitar
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.18,0:24:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就会成为新一代卡洛儿 金?\Nand you think you're the new Carole-fucking-King?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.43,0:24:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我只是觉得一个制作人告诉一个歌手如何穿着\NNo. I just think that an A&R man telling an artist how they should dress
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.41,0:24:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,如何给人印象简直是瞎扯\Nor come across is total bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.06,0:24:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,观众也不希望看到那些花哨的 他们想要的是真实\NPeople don't want that，They want authenticity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.33,0:24:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,行 你要真实是吧\NOkay, babe. Authenticity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.50,0:24:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,给我一个音乐人你认为是能通过你的真实测试\NGive me the name of one artist that you think passes your authenticity test.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.36,0:24:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- 迪伦 - 迪伦 他是你能想到的最真实的艺术家?\N- Dylan. - Dylan. That is the most cultivated artist you could have thought of?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.41,0:24:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,看看他的头发 他的墨镜 甚至他的脸都会十年变一次\NLook at his hair. His sunglasses. He changes his look every decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.65,0:24:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,兰迪 纽曼\NRandy Newman.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.04,0:25:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我真的很喜欢兰迪 纽曼 好吧 那算你赢了\NI fucking love Randy Newman. Okay, you got me on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.62,0:25:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,听着\NListen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.00,0:25:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我并不是说你不能\NI am not saying that you can't be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.41,0:25:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,达到这个行业的顶端\Na real bona fide motherfucker in this business.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.09,0:25:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,但是你要不惜一切代价\NBut you got to do whatever it takes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.79,0:25:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,让人们看你表演\Nand get people in to see your shows
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.94,0:25:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,让你的音乐搞出一番大事业来\Nwhere the music can start to do its real work.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.06,0:25:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊 我们到底在讨论些什么\NOh my God. What were we even talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.77,0:25:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你又不能签我 我也不想被签\NYou can't sign me. And I don't want to be signed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.55,0:25:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这样!为什么不喜欢被签呢?\NThats right. What's not to like?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.92,0:25:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,来 走吧\NCome on, let' get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.13,0:25:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,糟糕 不过你得付一下酒钱\NAh, shit. You're gonna have to get these beers, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.51,0:25:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 那很高兴认识你\NOK. So it was really nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.01,0:25:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你要去哪?\NWhere you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.08,0:25:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,回去睡觉啊 明天还要赶飞机\NTo sleep. I have a plane to catch tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.11,0:25:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,去哪?\NWhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.10,0:25:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- 家 - 为什么?\N- Home. - Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.72,0:25:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经厌倦这座城市了 我想要回大学了\NBecause I'm sick of this city and I want to go back to Uni.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.92,0:25:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,拜托 没有人会就这样来到纽约\NOh, come on. No one comes to New York
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.46,0:25:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,然后什么都不做就离开了\Nand just leaves without something terrible happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.02,0:25:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了?发生了什么事情?\NWhat? What happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.74,0:26:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 来跟我说说吧 我又不是什么悲惨的陌生人\NCome on. You can share with me. I' m no stranger to misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.31,0:26:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,你就来我们公司录个样本给我合伙人听听\NJust come to my label and let me play your demo to my partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.48,0:26:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,如果行不通的话\NIf it doesn't work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.59,0:26:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,就让我来付改签机票的钱\NI will personally pay to change your ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.79,0:26:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,为何不在纽约多呆一天放声大哭?\NWhat's one more day in New York for crying out loud?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.07,0:26:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,反正你回家了也是闷闷不乐的\NYou're just probably gonna go home and mope around anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.53,0:26:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 好吧\NAll right. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.64,0:26:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我回家考虑一下\NI'm gonna go home and think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.36,0:26:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我明早再打电话给你\NAnd, I'll call you either way tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.41,0:26:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,行么?\NOK?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.55,0:26:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- 赞 - 是啊\N- Good answer. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.50,0:26:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- 非常高兴认识你 - 我也是\N- It was very nice to meet you. - Yes, pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.53,0:26:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,是我的荣幸\NPleasure's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.02,0:26:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你有我电话的吧? - 有\N- You've got my number, right? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.75,0:27:36.75,顶部,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&HFF00FF&}Lost Stars - Keira Knightley{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.00,0:27:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please don't see \N请不要嘲笑 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.00,0:27:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just a girl caught up in dreams \N这只不过是一个沉浸在梦 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.00,0:27:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and fantasies \N与幻想中的女孩 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.00,0:27:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please see me reaching out \N好好看看我吧 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.00,0:28:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}for someone I can see \N伸出双臂去拥抱那些看不见的人 \N{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.00,0:28:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Take my hand let's see \N牵着我的手 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.70,0:28:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}where we wake up tomorrow \N看看明天我们会在哪里醒来 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.30,0:28:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Best laid plans sometimes \N缜密的计划有时 \N{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.30,0:28:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it's just a one night stand \N莫过于一夜的陪伴 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.30,0:28:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd be damned Cupid's demanding \N爱已消失 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.40,0:28:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}back his arrow \N我已心碎 {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.21,0:28:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 是Dave么?\NHi, Dave?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.91,0:28:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 我是Jill 我是唱片公司的接待员\NHi, I'm Jill. I work in hospitality with the label.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.49,0:28:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- 很高兴认识你 - 我也是\N- Nice to meet you. - Nice to meet you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.35,0:28:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你好 很高兴认识你\NHi, nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.96,0:28:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我来拿吧 跟我来这边 谢谢你 Marco\NGot it. Right this way. Thank you, Marco.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.38,0:28:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你们会很喜欢这所公寓 非常高档\NI think you're really gonna like the apartment. It's very high end.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.22,0:28:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- 抱歉 你是Dave Kohl吗? - 是的\N- I'm sorry. Are you emm...You're Dave Kohl. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.25,0:28:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你看!我说是的吧!\NYeah. I told you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.88,0:28:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们几天前看了你的电影 很喜欢你的那首歌\NWe saw your film the other day. I so love your songs in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.33,0:28:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 这是我女朋友Gretta 她也写歌\NThank you. This is Gretta, my girlfriend. She writes songs too.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.90,0:28:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,真好!请问能帮我们拍张照么 棒极了 按一下这个键就好\NAh, cool! Would you mind taking our photograph? That'd be so awesome. Just that button right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.18,0:29:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好了 很不错 - 谢谢\N- Yeah, it's a good one. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.39,0:29:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,恐怕你得慢慢习惯起来了\NYou're gonna have to get used to that, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.22,0:29:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这部电影在纽约都卖光了 太疯狂了\NThis movie is selling out all over town. It's pretty crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.52,0:29:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真是难以置信 - 不 这可是真的\N- Unbelievable. - Oh, no. It's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.88,0:29:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,好啦 就是这儿啦\NAll right, here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.49,0:29:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,希望你们会喜欢\NWe hope you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.43,0:29:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,冰箱里面吃的也已经买好了\NYour fridge in here is stocked with food.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.85,0:29:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,桌上有两串钥匙\NThere are two sets of keys on the table in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.16,0:29:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,这上面有司机的号码还有我的 我就放在这\NThis is your driver's number and my cell phone number.I'll leave that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.47,0:29:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你们中午要来公司和大家见个面\NYou're due at the label later this afternoon to meet everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.03,0:29:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我们会带你们在工作室里转转\NAnd then we'll take a tour around the studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.63,0:29:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你们也许想睡一会儿\NSo, probably want to catch up on your sleep before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.48,0:29:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我就先走了好么?\NI'll leave you to it. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.41,0:29:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- 很高兴认识你 Gretta - 我也是\N- Pleased to meet you, Gretta. - Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.40,0:29:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,这地方挺一般的\NThis place is a shithole.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.55,0:30:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我能问你件事么 - 当然\N- Hey. Can I ask you something? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.05,0:30:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我要不要先离开一两个星期\NShould I have come over in a week or two
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.81,0:30:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,让你自己好好适应这里?\Nand let you settle in first and get used to everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.00,0:30:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不要 - 你确定吗? - 是啊 没有你我什么都做不了 这里挺可怕的\N- No. - Are you sure? - Yeah. I don't know if I could do this without you. It's kind of scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.13,0:30:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我这么说会不会太娘炮?\NAm I a wimp for saying that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.36,0:30:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,你们来啦\NHey, there he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.25,0:30:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨 Dave 你好么\NBig Dave. What's up, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.23,0:30:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你 Gretta\NGood to see you. Gretta.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.53,0:30:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 进来吧\NCome on in, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.71,0:30:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,让Dave坐在最前面\NPut Dave at the head of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.89,0:30:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,太棒了\NAll right. I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.02,0:30:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你们和大家见过了么? - 大家好\N- You guys meet everyone? - Hi everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.30,0:30:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这位是我的助手Mim 很漂亮吧\NMy assistant, Mim. The beautiful Mim.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.26,0:30:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,这位是市场部的Milred\NThis is Mildred from Marketing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.19,0:30:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,还有媒体营销的Billy\NBilly there is Social Media.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.91,0:30:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,团队里剩下的人以后你们都会接触到的\NThe rest of the gang, you'll meet, spend time with.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.21,0:30:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那么 Gretta你也能在乐队里弹一两首歌吧?\NSo, Gretta you're gonna play guitar on a track or two, I hope, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.87,0:30:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- 可以的 如果Dave想要的话 - 是的\N- Oh yeah, sure. If Dave wants. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.63,0:30:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,这些年来Gretta一直在我一起做音乐\NGretta and I have been writing together for a couple years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.13,0:30:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至到这电影完成之前.\NEven before the film came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.34,0:31:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我也很乐意去尝试表演些她的歌\NSo, I would love for us to try a couple of her songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.30,0:31:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你也参与了这次音乐电影的歌曲编写吗?\NDid you write on the film with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.23,0:31:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,不 没有\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.79,0:31:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是我们在电影拍完后写的那首 对吧?Dave?\NThat's the sound we're after is from the movie, right? Dave?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.50,0:31:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是的 - 是吗?对吗?没错? - 对 没错\N- Of course. - Oui? Si? Capice? - Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.24,0:31:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Gretta给我提供了许多灵感\NGretta is very much apart of the inspiration behind everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.35,0:31:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,她不仅仅是我的女友\NShe's not just my girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.36,0:31:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,她确实也是我的一部分\NI just wanted to include her.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.13,0:31:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,说白了 我只是一直跟随着他\NJust to be completely clear. I'm just tagging along on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.13,0:31:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴能来这儿\NI'm really happy to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.98,0:31:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,更开心能和Dave一起工作\NAnd happy to accompany Daveon a couple of tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.37,0:31:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,这姑娘嘴真甜 是吧 我喜欢\NHow sweet is this girl? I love that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.93,0:31:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这两人真棒!我爱他们\NHow great are these guys? I love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.04,0:31:52.04,顶部,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&H3334FF&}No One Else Like You - Adam Levine{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.93,0:32:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 我会继续巡演乐队\NYeah, I'm going on tour with the band.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.75,0:32:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,滚石杂志\NRolling Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.23,0:32:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 谢谢了 聊得很开心 谢谢\NYeah. Thank you so much. It was great talking to you. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.31,0:32:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么东西?\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.74,0:32:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是抹茶 - 抹茶? - 是啊\N- That's matcha tea. - Matcha tea? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.66,0:32:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,它含有大约400万的抗氧化物质\NIt's got like four million antioxidants in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.02,0:32:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我的天 喝起来像尿 - 那是我喜欢的\N- Oh my God, it tastes like piss. - I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.98,0:32:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,武士去打战前都会喝抹茶\NThe samurais used to drink it before they went into battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.08,0:32:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你又不是武士 你是一个音乐人\NYou're not a samurai. You're a songwriter.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.30,0:32:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但我也很喜欢武士\NWell, I'm kind of like a samurai.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.71,0:32:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗?\NAre you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.05,0:32:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我要把这拿去给他们了\NI'm gonna give these to the guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.00,0:32:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们星期一要去洛杉矶一个星期 - 我们要去洛杉矶?\N- Oh, hey. We gotta go to LA for a week on Monday. - We're going to LA?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.26,0:32:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,不 抱歉 是我和公司的人 他们在那有办公室\NNo. Sorry. It's just with some of the label guys. They have an office out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.52,0:32:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,他们想让我见见视频导演\NThey want me to meet this video director guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.37,0:32:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,还有我很想让你听听这个 好吗?\NBut, in the meantime, I'd really like you to listen to this. So, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.99,0:32:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,好的 对不起 我先去送咖啡\NYes, I'm sorry. I'll deliver coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.26,0:32:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,伙计们 我们再来一次好吗?\NHey guys, can we do this again, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.38,0:32:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,第二次 开始\NTake two. And rolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.82,0:33:01.32,顶部,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&H3AF5F8&\1a&H00&}No One Else Like You - Adam Levine{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.32,0:33:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一切都刚刚好吗?\NIs everything just right?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.05,0:33:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不想让你觉得我太赶时间\NDon't want you thinking that I'm in a hurry{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.60,0:33:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我并不会害怕\NI won't stay afraid{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.32,0:33:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我有着让我担心的愿景\NI had this vision that has got me worried{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.05,0:33:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为每个人都想要某个人\N'Cause everyone wants someone{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.09,0:33:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这些陈词滥调都是真的\NThat's one cliché that's true{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.67,0:33:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}除了你我真的谁都不想要\NExcept you I want no one{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.62,0:33:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}除非那个人还是你\NUnless that someone's you{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.76,0:33:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}看你来像你 感觉起来还是你\NIt looks like you. Feels like you{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.11,0:33:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}笑起来像你 我希望那个人像你一样\NSmiles like you. I want someone just like you{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.35,0:33:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}真诚而且永远那么清纯\NTrue and through Forever blue{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.20,0:33:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为没有人像你一样\N'Cause there's no one else like{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.50,0:34:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.05,0:34:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,看看是谁!\NLook at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.56,0:34:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这三个月他一直呆在工作室\NHe has the studio for three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.59,0:34:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我们会去巡演 所以 我们估计要呆个半年\NAnd then we go on tour. So I think we're staying for six?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.34,0:34:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,真是不敢相信 你简直就像是一个摇滚明星\NThis is unbelievable. You're total rock stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.25,0:34:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- 哪个唱片公司和他在合作? - Electric lady\NWhich studio is he working with? Electric lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.21,0:34:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- 卧槽啊! - 很酷是吧? - 你在开玩笑吗\N- Oh fuck off! - It's really cool, isn't it? - Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.77,0:34:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的房间\NSo this is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.20,0:34:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这很棒啊 - 是啊 就像老笑话讲的一样\N- Oh, this is lovely. - Yeah, it's like that old joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.49,0:34:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,有开门的钥匙却还是要破窗进来\NYou put the key in the door,you break a window.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.34,0:34:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我的天 看看你的这些东西\NMy god, look at all this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.08,0:35:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 有很多工作室正在升级\NYeah, a lot of the studios are upgrading.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.77,0:35:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- 都不要这些东西了 我都可以靠这些录一张专辑了 - 那很酷诶\N- So practically giving stuff away. I can record an album here soon. - Well, that'd be cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.83,0:35:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你的CD成堆了\NLook at you, you've got CDs.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.27,0:35:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 我刚把我所有的磁带扔掉了 坐在这儿吧\NYeah. I just phased out all my cassettes. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.84,0:35:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是很怀旧啊\NHow retro of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.00,0:35:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你要威士忌还是水?\NI have whiskey. Or water?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.84,0:35:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,威士忌!\NWhiskey, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.21,0:35:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,就知道你\NOf course you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.27,0:35:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,看看你都有什么\NLook what you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.34,0:35:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这里的人都为这张专辑疯狂了\NPeople are going crazy for that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.22,0:35:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,当我表演的时候大家知道\NWhen I play a show and the people know
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.38,0:35:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,当我去布里斯托尔大学之后 他们问的第一件事就是认不认识你的男朋友\NI went to college in Bristol. The first thing they ask is if I know your boyfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.32,0:35:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,可不是吗?我回家后就成了"Dave Kohl的女朋友"\NYeah, tell me about it. I'm becoming "Dave Kohl's girlfriend" back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.33,0:35:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我就想说"我们本来是个团队的 到底发生了什么?"\NI'm like, "Hello, we used to be a team. What happened?"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.98,0:35:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?他们把你的歌放到电影里去了\NOh, you know what they say. Get your songs in a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.05,0:35:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 然后 这就是我的全部了 天知道我这样过了多久 - 我喜欢\N- So, this is me. This is where I've been for God knows how long. - I love that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.03,0:35:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是吗? - 是啊 - 你看见那张床了么?这是我自己做的 是我的床\N- Do you? - Yeah. - Did you see the bed? I made that bed. That bed is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.98,0:35:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- 太厉害了 你怎么爬上去的? - 跳上去呗\N- That's very impressive. How'd you get up there? - I vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.20,0:35:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,撑个杆子跳上去吗?\NYou vault? With a pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.34,0:35:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,不用杆子 我用滑板的 一个滑板就行\NNo, no pole. I do it in one straight...one straight luge.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.37,0:35:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,除非我喝醉了 那我就掉下来了\NUnless I'm drunk. In which case. It's off on a dismount.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.35,0:36:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这张专辑的背面 他拿吉他的方式\NIt's the back I like. It's like he's holding a guitar.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.14,0:36:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,但他想让你觉得这是他老二\NBut he wants you to think it's his penis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.53,0:36:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,他说"看 这是一把吉他\NHe's saying, Look, it's a guitar.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.27,0:36:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但并不是这样 这是我老二的实际尺寸"\NBut it's not. This is the actual size of my penis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.35,0:36:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}为什么不呢?\NWhy, no?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.24,0:36:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为必须要让你发挥一下 以同样的方式 让你也玩一玩\NI am gonna shoot this because you have to play thatexactly the way you just played it.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.33,0:36:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}好了 那你来弹吉他\NOkay, you play the guitar.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.66,0:36:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为没伴奏我可唱不起来\NBecause I can't do that when that thing's on.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.21,0:36:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- 是G调哦 - 我知道是G - 我不喜欢G\N- It's in G. - I know G. - I don't like G.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.92,0:36:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}没关系 你知道吗?你必须克服它\NIt doesn't matter. And you know what? You have to get over this.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.31,0:36:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是一次锻炼\NThis is an exercise.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.24,0:36:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}好的 准备好了吗?\NYes. Ready?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.16,0:36:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}慢一点\NSlower.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.92,0:36:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please don't see.\N这只不过是{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.30,0:36:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just a girl caught up in dreams and fantasies.\N一个小女孩坐观空仰梦幻{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.60,0:36:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please see me\N我要用心{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.37,0:37:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}reaching out for someone I can't see.\N触碰身边的意中人{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.99,0:37:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Take my hand.\N牵起我的手吧{\i}
