Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.56,0:57:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,太感谢了\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.27,0:57:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,她来了\NThat's her.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.94,0:57:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是Gretta 就是我和你说的那个音乐人 - 你好吗?\N- This is Gretta. She's the song writer I was telling you about. - How are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.30,0:57:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,那个穿蓝色T恤的帅哥是谁?\NSo who was the cute guy? The one in the blue shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.33,0:57:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Greg 你注意到他了?\NGreg. You noticed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.20,0:58:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,当然啊 他那么帅怎么可能注意不到\NSure. Who wouldn't? He's gorgeous.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.76,0:58:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,他真的遥不可及\NHe's totally out of our league.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.70,0:58:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你无法接近他?\NHe's out of your league?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.28,0:58:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,但看着并不像这样啊\NHe didn't look out of your league.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.57,0:58:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,忽视他吧\NIgnore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.44,0:58:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么让别人注意到你在忽视他们\NHow can you get someone to notice you're ignoring them
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.74,0:58:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他们在忽视你呢?\Nif they're ignoring you?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.94,0:58:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他没有忽视你啦 你那么漂亮\NHe's not ignoring you. You're beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.13,0:58:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他知道你在这儿 他只是在等待靠近你的机会\NHe knows you're there. He's just hedging his bets.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.35,0:58:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但你必须确定你是真的很喜欢他\NYou have to be sure that you actually like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.83,0:58:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,确定他不是那种只适合在学校里交往的人\NHe's not just the guy in school to be seen with.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.53,0:58:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我确实挺喜欢他的\NNo, I do really like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.06,0:58:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,那你快想个办法让他约你出去啊\NWell, then, you have to find a way to get him to ask you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.81,0:58:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,那我该怎么做?\NYes, but how?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.42,0:58:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,首先不要穿得像个很随便的女生啊\NWell, for starters, stop dressing like you're totally easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.05,0:58:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我还以为这样看起来会性感点 这可是American Apparel的衣服啊\NI thought this was sort of sexy. It's American Apparel.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.45,0:58:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,的确是性感的 非常 非常性感\NIt is sort of sexy. It's very, very sexy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.16,0:58:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- 但这看起来一点神秘感都没有 你懂么? - 也许吧\N- But it doesn't leave much to the imagination. You know? - I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.25,0:59:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你想去逛街吗? - 好啊 - 是吗? - 恩\N- You want to go shopping? - I do. - Yeah? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.12,0:59:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好的 - 我们要去逛街\N- Okay, good. - We're going shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.96,0:59:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谢谢 - 谢谢\N- Thank you. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.88,0:59:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- 祝你的专辑好运 听起来很不错 - 谢谢\N- Good luck with the rest of your album. It sounds cool. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.91,0:59:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你有钥匙吗? - 有\N- You have your key? - Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.47,0:59:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你也可以来加入我们录音啊\NHey you should come sing on a track?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.79,0:59:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,可我不会唱歌\NI can't sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.20,0:59:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我会弹点吉他\NI can play like a bit of guitar.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.50,0:59:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,真的吗?我们周四会开始录歌\NCan you? We're doing one on Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.33,0:59:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- 挺简单的 你可以来试下啊 - 爸爸可以吗?\N- It will be really simple. You should come and play. - Can I dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.51,0:59:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,我再考虑一下\NI need to contemplate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.07,0:59:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你这是在干什么?干嘛这样做?\NWhat are you doing? That ain't cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.08,0:59:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我都不知道她吉他有没好到能录在专辑里\NI don't know if she can play guitar well enough to play on a track.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.28,0:59:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 如果到时候弹不好会让她很尴尬的 - 放心吧 挺简单的 让她来吧\N- I don’t won’t to embarrass her. What if she can't play? - Look, it's going to be easy. Let her do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.47,1:00:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谁啊? - 是我\N- Yeah? - Hey, babe.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.69,1:00:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet呢?\NWhere's Violet?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.43,1:00:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Violet?\NViolet?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.59,1:00:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我在想啊 你认为我周四录歌让她来弹吉他怎样?\NI was wondering...You think it would be cool if she came and played guitar on a song I'm recording on Thursday?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.73,1:00:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,她弹的蛮难听的\NShe's terrible on guitar.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.79,1:00:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- 应该不差吧 - 她真的很糟糕 - 我觉得应该没问题\N- She's not bad. - She's terrible. - I think she'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.42,1:00:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么时候? - 五点 你能带她来吗?\N- When will she...? - Five o'clock. Will you bring her?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.31,1:00:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你决定吧 - 好\N- It's up to you. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.77,1:00:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我把地址发给你 要不你也来吧\NI'll text you the address. Why don't you come to?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.34,1:00:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,不可能\NNo way.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.60,1:00:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 会很有趣的\NCome on. Just come. It'll be fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.57,1:00:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- 而且我希望你能来 - 我考虑下吧\N- I want you to come. - I'll think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.11,1:00:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我可能会去的 - 谢谢\N- I'll come, maybe. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.16,1:01:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,今天很开心能见到你和Violet在一起\NIt's nice to see you with Violet today.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.87,1:01:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不能经常看见她 你一定很痛苦吧\NIt must be hard not seeing her more.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.93,1:01:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\NYeah.It's...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.48,1:01:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,那你为什么不经常去看看她?\NSo why don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.20,1:01:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,很显然她需要爸爸在她身边\NShe obviously really needs her father around.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.16,1:01:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你在当社工教育我么?\NWhat are you the fucking Social Services now?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.24,1:01:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,没啦 我只是想说...\NNo. I mean I'm just saying...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.82,1:01:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,对你来说离开一定很痛苦吧\NIt must have been fairly tense for you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.31,1:01:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,尤其是当看到她现在有多么需要你的时候\NEspecially seeing as how much she obviously wants you around.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.63,1:01:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我要走了 明早见吧\NI'm gonna split. I'll see you tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.43,1:01:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,搞什么啊\NFuck, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.90,1:02:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Dan?抱歉 我错了\NDan? Hey, look. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.46,1:02:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,那你想要我怎样?你在玩什么小把戏?\NWhat do you want from me? What game are you playing?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.24,1:02:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么意思?我只是...\NWhat does that mean? I just...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.33,1:02:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,- 什么? - 只是我今天看见她那么可爱\N- What? - I saw how sweet she was today
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.20,1:02:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,觉得你不能和她在一起实在是太可惜了\Nand I just felt sorry for you being away from that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.24,1:02:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你有病吧 你就自己做出这样的判断\NThat is such a crock of shit. You were back there judging me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.29,1:02:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你说的好像是我离开他们...\NYou think that I left that relationship...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.36,1:02:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,就因为我是个自私的混蛋吗?\Nbecause I'm some sort of selfish, depressed prick?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.01,1:02:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然我就是这样\NWhich I am, by the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.38,1:02:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,没啊 我不认为你是一个自私的混蛋\NNo. I don't think you're a selfish, depressed prick.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.31,1:02:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是觉得你让自己的问题影响到你的生活罢了\NI think you've let your troubles get in the way of your entire life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.22,1:02:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你太幼稚了\NOh, babe. You're really showing your age right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.37,1:02:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你完全不清楚两个经历18年婚姻生活的夫妻\NYou have no idea what happens between two people
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.33,1:02:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,究竟发生了什么事情\Nafter 18 years of marriage.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.29,1:02:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,这是因为你愿意和一个出轨了的傻逼交往\NAnd because you're willing to hang around for some asshole
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.33,1:02:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,就认为全天下的男人都是这样的吗?那是你自己的事了\Nafter he totally betrayed you, that's your business.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.93,1:02:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,不 我很抱歉 你说的没错\NOh no. I'm sorry. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.74,1:02:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我为那段感情付出了很多!\NI put a lot of time and effort into that relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.33,1:02:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,不!我不会因为一点小障碍就离开的\NAnd no! I'm not walking away just because of a bump in the road!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.17,1:02:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,小障碍?\NBump in the road?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.33,1:03:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我离开是因为她伤透了我的心\NI left that relationship 'cause I was having a nervous breakdown.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.23,1:03:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,她出去跟别的男人上床\NAnd she was out there fucking some other guy
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.30,1:03:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,而且她打算和那个男的在一起\Nplanning how she was gonna start a whole new life with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.30,1:03:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,而当时我却在照顾我的孩子!\Nwhen I was here taking care of my kid!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.20,1:03:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你一点儿也不清楚你在说什么!\NYou have no fucking clue what you're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.16,1:03:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么都不知道!\NYou know nothing!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.64,1:03:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,她就出差了一年\NShe goes a year up to work on a junket.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.27,1:03:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,就爱上了一个歌手\NAnd she ends up meeting and falling in love with this singer.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.28,1:03:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他们爱得不能自拔 产生了爱情的冲动和火花\NBang. Boom. Thunder, lightning, fireworks. The whole bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.12,1:03:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,他们计划各自回家\NAnd the arrangement was that they were gonna come back
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.49,1:03:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉各自的配偶关于他们相爱的事情\Nand tell their partners that they had fallen in love
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.01,1:03:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,他们还准备共度一生\Nand they're gonna spend the rest of their lives together.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.22,1:03:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,等我赶到机场迎接她时\NAnd so I go to the airport to pick her up
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.29,1:03:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,她就把一切都向我坦白了\Nand she just comes out with it first off. Whole story.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.26,1:03:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,第二天 她的行李就都打包好了\NThen next day her bags are all packed
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.23,1:04:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们就告诉了Violet发生了什么 - 然后呢 发生了什么事?\N- and we're telling Violet what's going to happen. - So what did happen?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.27,1:04:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,他忍着对这份爱情的渴望 登上了飞机又重新回到自己的生活中\NHe choked. He got on the airplane. Went back to his life.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.37,1:04:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,他关掉了手机 然后就这样消失了\NTurned his phone off and she never heard from him again.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.05,1:04:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我搬到了另一个房间去住\NI move into another bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.19,1:04:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,而她则在等待一个永远不会打来的电话\NShe's waiting around for a phone call that never comes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.92,1:04:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我很生气...\NAnd I turn into a...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.82,1:04:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,然后就变成了现在这个样子\NI lose my shit a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.39,1:04:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对不起 - 没事\N- So sorry. - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.93,1:04:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,也许干音乐这行的\NMaybe people in the music industry don't
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.07,1:04:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,就不能成为一个好的伴侣或者是一个好父亲\Njust don't make good life partners or fathers.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.97,1:04:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 看起来是的\NYeah. It certainly looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.56,1:04:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不能成为一个好爸爸倒说不定 我觉得你是一个非常好的父亲 - 是啊\N- I didn't mean about the father's bit. You make a very good father. - Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.37,1:04:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,可能只是不是好搭档\NMaybe just not a good partner.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.57,1:04:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,这个是什么\NWhat is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.73,1:04:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,这个?这是个分频器\NThis? That's a splitter.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.50,1:04:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,一个源能插两个耳机\NFor two headphones go into one input.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.77,1:04:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这是我第一次和Miriam约会时用的 - It is?\N- It's actually from my first date with Miriam. - 是吗?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.57,1:05:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你们在哪相遇的?\NWhere'd you meet?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.72,1:05:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我们听着她的CD 在城市里一起慢慢散步\NWe walked all over the city, listening to her CD player.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.73,1:05:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我感觉我们整个晚上都没怎么说过话\NI don't think we said more than two words to each other the whole night.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.63,1:05:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那时是除夕 两个月后 我们就结婚了\NThat was New Year's Eve and we were married two months later.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.63,1:05:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,挺好的\NThat's lovely.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.58,1:05:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你手机里有什么歌?\NWhat kind of music you got on your phone?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.69,1:05:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我不会跟你分享我的音乐的 绝对不会\NI'm not giving you access to my music library. I'm really not.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.69,1:05:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- 里面有很多尴尬的歌 - 我也是\N- There's a lot of embarrassing, very guilty pleasures in there. - Mine too.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.79,1:05:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以通过他听的歌了解这个人的很多方面\NYou can tell a lot about a person by what's on their playlist.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.09,1:05:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我就是知道这一点 才让我觉得担心的\NI know you can. That's what's worrying me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.60,1:05:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,所以能听听看吗?\NSo are we gonna do this?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.28,1:05:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,好 来吧!\NOkay. Let's do it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.18,1:06:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,听起来不错!\NThis is a really good choice!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.75,1:06:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 很完美 对不对? - 是啊\N- Oh yeah. Genius. Perfect. Right? - Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.11,1:06:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不!不对!\NOh no! I forgot the words!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.23,1:06:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这时候该跳舞了 - 什么?\N- Okay! Okay, we've got to dance. - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.96,1:06:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我们必须要跳舞!\NWe've got to dance!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.69,1:06:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好吧 我们要跳舞了 - 我们要跳舞了!\N- Okay, we've got to dance. - We've gotta dance!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.94,1:06:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,来这边\NThis way.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.43,1:07:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我怕你会觉得这首歌有点俗气\NI'm quite frightened 'cause you might find this cheesy
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.36,1:07:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,但是这是我最喜欢的电影里的一首歌\Nbut it is one of my favorite songs from one of my favorite films.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.96,1:08:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你准备好了吗?\NAre you ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.44,1:08:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,很棒对吧?\NIt's good, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.63,1:08:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这就是我为什么喜欢音乐 - 什么?\N- That's what I love about music. - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.63,1:08:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,生活中最普通的一幕 突然间\NOne of the most banal scenes is suddenly invested
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.52,1:08:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,就充满了这么多的意义\Nwith so much meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.67,1:08:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的那些琐事\NAll these banalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.63,1:08:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,因为音乐\NThey're suddenly turned into these...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.78,1:08:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他们突然变成了\Nthese beautiful
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.77,1:08:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,闪亮无暇的珍珠\Neffervescent pearls.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.91,1:09:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须说 当我越来越老时 这些珍珠\NI've gotta say, as I've gotten older these pearls
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.68,1:09:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说越来越稀有珍贵\Nare just becoming increasingly more and more rare to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.35,1:09:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,线比珍珠链多?\NMore string than pearls?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.66,1:09:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,那你要收集到够多的珍珠才行\NYou've got to travel over a lot more string to get to the pearls.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.16,1:09:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,这一刻便是珍珠啊 Gretta\NThis moment is a pearl, Gretta.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.56,1:09:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,也算吧?\NIt sort of is, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.65,1:09:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,对 这些都是珍珠\NAll of this has been a pearl.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.56,1:10:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 大家好! - Hi\N- Hey guys! - 嗨
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.26,1:10:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,你好啊 Steve\NHello Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.72,1:10:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- 快来看看这个 你男友刚获得了个音乐奖 - 不可能吧\N- Come on and check it out. Your boyfriend just won a Music Gong. - No way.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.48,1:10:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,简直不敢相信\NYou won't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.69,1:10:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,他的脸怎么了\NHe's done something to his face.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.71,1:10:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,哇 非常感谢大家\NWow. Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.91,1:10:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我有点困惑和惊讶我能获得这个奖 这太棒了\NI'm a bit taken aback by this. This is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.77,1:10:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但这证明了一个人\NIt just proves that a guy from nowhere
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.65,1:10:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,可以真的成功如果他一直追求在梦想\Ncan actually make it if he follows his dreams.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.78,1:10:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,老实讲 这段话\NI've been practicing this speech
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.68,1:10:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经在浴室里拿着我的香波练习了无数遍了\Ninto a shampoo bottle in the shower my entire life.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.58,1:10:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- 天 谢谢你们 - 胡子不错 你个傻逼\N- Gosh. Thank you. - Nice beard, you fucking loser.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.72,1:10:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,什么梦想?\NWhat dreams?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.76,1:10:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我们从来没有做过那样的梦想 我不记得有那样的梦想\NWe never had those dreams. I don't remember those dreams.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.80,1:10:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你怎么知道? - 因为我了解他\N- How do you know? - Because, I know him.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.90,1:10:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,也许是他个人的梦想\NMaybe they were private dreams.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.10,1:10:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,只不过他从来没告诉过你\NMaybe he just never told you about them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.19,1:10:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,可是我跟那个人一起生活了五年呀?\NWho was I living with for the last five years?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.21,1:10:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,你一直在跟一个摇滚明星生活 只是他并不自知罢了\NBaby, you've been living with a rock star. Only he didn't know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.22,1:10:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,无所谓 但现在他找到了自我 我告诉你\NIt didn't matter. But now that he does, I've gotta tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.74,1:10:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,这些人都很爱这种感觉\Nthese people get married to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.19,1:11:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,他们爱上了音乐 爱上了聚光灯 走上了这条路\NThey fall in love with the music. They fall in love with the lights. They fall in love with the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.94,1:11:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,爱上了一切乱七八糟的东西 无论他如何努力\NAll that shit. And no matter how hard he tries
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.90,1:11:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他都不会让女人快乐起来的\Nhe's never gonna be able to make a woman happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.19,1:11:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好了 明早见 - 再见\N- See you in the morning. - See you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.17,1:11:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他为什么这样做呢?\NWhy would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.37,1:11:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道 谁会这样做呢?\NI don't know. Why would anyone?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.76,1:11:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我来告诉你他为什么这样做吧\NI'll tell you why he did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.31,1:11:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他想成为那种会说\N'Cause he wants to look like the guy who doesn't realize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.31,1:11:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"我的胡子这么长了!\N"Oh! I've grown a beard!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.11,1:11:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我太忙了 沉浸在歌曲创作中\NI was so busy, lost inside myself writing music
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.19,1:11:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,没有意识到我的胡须已经长到脖子这里了"\NI didn't realize I'd grown a beard the size of my neck."
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.31,1:11:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,这样想来我那时真是太傻了\NI'm gonna sound quite cheesy over it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.63,1:11:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,像个傻瓜一样爱着他\NI loved him like a fool.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.13,1:11:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我可不认为你是个傻瓜 我感觉那听起来像首很不错的歌\NI don't think that's cheesy. I think that sounds like a phenomenal song.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.11,1:11:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是吗? - 是的 就像一首歌\N- Does it? - It sounds like a song.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.13,1:11:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得你应该写出来 现在就写出来\NI think it sounds like a song that you should write right now.\NYou should write it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.14,1:11:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,写下来\NWrite it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.12,1:11:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 写下来 用你的灵感 快说你现在真有灵感 - 好的 我现在灵感喷发\N- Write it down, 'cause you're in the zone. Say it, I'm in the zone. - I'm in the zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.29,1:11:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,不要写那种你是什么漂亮的英国女孩\NDon't say it like you're those posh English girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.26,1:11:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,来纽约写歌 就写我现在灵感爆发\NSay it like someone in New York. Say, I'm in the fucking zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.16,1:11:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你写下来"我就是感觉来了才写歌" - 我就是感觉来了才写歌\N- Say "I'm in the fucking zone." - I'm in the fucking zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.14,1:11:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我要写首歌 不管是什么\NI've gotta write a song. And I don't give a shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.16,1:11:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我就是要写一首歌 - 好啦 快闭嘴\N- I'm gonna write a song. - No, actually shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.21,1:12:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 我不说话了 我不说话\NAll right. I'm shushing. I'm shushing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.14,1:12:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,已拨 好了 准备开始\NDialing. All right, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.57,1:12:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,打开免提\NSpeaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.10,1:12:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我是Dave Kohl\NHey, this is Dave Kohl.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.21,1:12:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我在忙着干大事接不了电话\NI am probably busy doing something awesome
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.93,1:12:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,有事请留言\Nso leave me a message
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.37,1:12:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但我也许永远也不会看\Nand I probably won't be able to get back to you at all. Ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.04,1:12:25.00,顶部,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&HD468F8&}Like a Fool - Keira Knightley {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.13,1:12:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们会时不时的在爱情中冒冒险\NWe take a chance from time to time{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.22,1:12:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有时简直就是自找麻烦\NAnd put our necks out on the line{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.32,1:12:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你已经打破了一个个\NAnd you have broken every promise{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.14,1:12:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}彼此间的承诺\Nthat we made{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.17,1:12:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}愚蠢的是我居然一直爱着你\NAnd I have loved you anyway{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.13,1:13:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}选择了这么一个好时机离开我\NTook a fine time to leave me hangin' out to dry{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.21,1:13:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}把我晾在一边\NUnderstand now I'm greivin'{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.99,1:13:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}走吧 别再浪费我的时间\NSo don't you waste my time{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.18,1:13:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你已经拿走了我的一切\NCause you have taken{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.31,1:13:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我的人生旅途就这么停止了\NAll the wind out from my sails{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.49,1:13:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}愚蠢的是我却一直爱着你\NAnd I have loved you just the same{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.88,1:13:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我们的爱刚刚萌发 你却这么走了\NWe finally find this then you're gone{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.11,1:13:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我只能继续追寻人生的美好\NBeen chasin' rainbows all along{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.55,1:13:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}而你却怪罪于我\NAnd you have cursed me{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.10,1:13:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}当我们都不应该被谴责的时候\NWhen there's no one left to blame{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.21,1:14:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}愚蠢的是我还是那么爱你\NAnd I have loved you just the same{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.10,1:14:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你已经打破了\NAnd you have broken{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.20,1:14:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一个个该死的规定\Nevery single fucking rule{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.14,1:14:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}愚蠢的是我居然还是那么爱你\NAnd I have loved you like a fool{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.31,1:14:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,再来首?\NOne more?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.20,1:16:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,介绍一下这是Miriam\NHey. Everybody! This is Miriam.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.14,1:16:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,这是Gretta\NThis is Gretta.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.45,1:16:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的女儿Violet\NThis is my daughter Violet.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.19,1:16:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Miriam 谢谢\NMiriam. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.13,1:16:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,这不算高吧\NIt's not too high is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.76,1:16:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这对贝斯来说不算高的吧\NIt's not too high for a bass. Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.71,1:16:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,如果要这样的话 根本不会有人想要玩贝斯\NNo one should play bass unless it's this high.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.10,1:16:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,要我调放大声音 还是这样就好?\NYou want me to set your amp or are you good?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.19,1:16:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,不不不 等等 等等\NHold up. Hold up. Hold up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.19,1:16:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Rachel 最开始的时候 加快一点没关系\NRachel. At the top, come in a little more gradually.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.25,1:16:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jimmy! - 什么事? - 给点力 - 好吧 我知道了\N- Bad Jimmy! - Yo, what's up? - Come on, man. - All right. I got you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.07,1:16:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- 警察不会追到这儿来的 让我听听低音 - 好好好 放心吧\N- The police ain't gonna get you up here. Let's hear that bass. - I got you, baby. I got you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.27,1:16:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,抱歉 等一等 你是不是能弹贝司?\NI'm sorry. Wait a minute. Do you play bass?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.27,1:16:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你跑题了 不行\NYou were out of tune. You are flat.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.19,1:16:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我在网上看见的 你以前好像是弹贝司的\NBecause I read on the internet that you used to play bass.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.29,1:16:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,所以既然已经让Violet弹吉他了\NIf we can get Violet doing some guitar on this.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.30,1:16:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这应该是家庭事务了吧\NThis should be a family affair.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.51,1:16:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我不弹贝斯所以我才是个制作人\NI'm a producer 'cause I don't play bass, baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.77,1:16:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 你得做的 你要弹的\NYes you are! You gotta do it. You gotta do it!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.29,1:16:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧!好吧!\NAll right! All right!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.29,1:16:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你想要弹的时候就插进来吧\NCome in whenever you want. You can wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.14,1:17:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,很简单的\NJust keep it simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.87,1:17:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道要弹什么\NI don't know if I'm gonna play.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.78,1:17:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,随便 你想怎么弹就怎么弹 好吗?\NWhatever. If you feel like it you do it. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.22,1:17:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,完全没问题的 不要有压力想着去怎么做\NIt's totally cool. But don't feel like you have to overdo it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.60,1:17:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,或者想去证明什么 这些家伙们都是的...\Nor prove anything to anybody. These guys are all...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.18,1:17:14.89,顶部,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dave Kohl\N语音邮件和未接来电{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.94,1:17:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,大伙们 抱歉 我们能休息五分钟吗?\NGuys. Sorry. Can we take five?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.85,1:17:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好的 休息五分钟吧 - 是五分钟 不是十分钟\N- All right. Let's take five. - Five, not ten.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.92,1:17:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我回纽约开演唱会了\NHey. I'm back in New York for a gig.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.57,1:17:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我听到你唱歌的电话留言了 我必须见你\NI got your singing message. I have to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.99,1:17:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,回我电话 请一定回我电话\NCall me. Please call me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.42,1:17:45.81,顶部,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&H78C437&}Tell Me If You Wanna Go Home - Keira Knightley{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.81,1:17:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也许你不必如此的友善\NOh maybe you don't have to kill so kind{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.82,1:17:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}假装来治愈我的心 但其实你并不会这样\Npretend to ease my mind when baby you won't{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.90,1:18:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}亲爱的 你不必甜言蜜语\NOh sugar, you don't have to be so sweet{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.86,1:18:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我知道你会遇见谁\NI know who you're going to meet{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.02,1:18:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}别说我不会知道\NDon't say that I don't{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.98,1:18:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}也许我不会让对你的回忆困扰我\NSo maybe I won't let your memory haunt me{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.41,1:18:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我会和孤独一起去梦游\NI'll be sleep walking with the lonely{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.86,1:18:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果你带我回家\NIf you taking me home{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.85,1:18:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}告诉我是否这是我自己的家\Ntell me if I'm back to my own{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.93,1:18:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}并且还给我曾经借给你的心\NGiving back a heart that's on loan{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.96,1:18:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果你想回家就告诉我\NJust tell me if you wanna go home{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.83,1:18:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}告诉我你想回家\NTell me if you wanna go home{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.95,1:18:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为我不太确定 (告诉我是否这是我自己的家)\N'cause I'm just not sure (tell me if I'm back to my own){\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.05,1:18:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果回到曾经\Nhow to get back there{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.89,1:18:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还给我曾借给你的心\NGiving back a heart that's on loan{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.83,1:19:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果你要带我回家\NIf you taking me home{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.81,1:19:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}请告诉我这就是我的家\Ntell me if I'm back to my own{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.87,1:19:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还给我曾借给你的心\NGiving back a heart that's on loan{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.41,1:19:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}告诉我你是否打算回家\Njust tell me if you wanna go wanna go wanna go wanna go wanna{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.94,1:19:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为我不太确定 我们是否回得到从前\N'cause I'm just not sure how to get back there{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.86,1:19:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}而且我再也无法承受 如果你不在那里\Nand I just can't bear if you're not there{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.05,1:19:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}因为我不太确定\N'cause I'm just not sure{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.05,1:19:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}告诉我是否回到我自己的家 (该怎么回去)\NTell me if I'm back to my own (How to get back there){\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.00,1:19:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还给我曾借给你的心 (只是我再也无法承受)\NGiving back a heart that's on loan (and I just can't bear){\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.42,1:19:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}如果你想回家就告诉我 (如果你不在那里)\NJust tell me if you wanna go home (if you're not there){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.42,1:19:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}(因为我不太确定)\N(Cause I'm just not sure) {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.20,1:19:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}(该怎么回去)\N(How to get back there) {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.46,1:19:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}(只是我再也无法承受)\N(And I just can't bear){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.62,1:19:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}(如果你不在那里)\N(If you're not there) {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.91,1:20:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,把该死的音乐关小点!\NTurn down that fucking music!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.90,1:20:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,再给我们三分钟!\NGive us three more minutes!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.23,1:20:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我报警了\NI'm calling the cops.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.00,1:20:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,别报警\NDon't call the cops.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.54,1:20:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我的天!Violet 太棒了!\NOh my God! Oh, Violet!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.48,1:21:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,警察来了!来吧 我们撤!\NAnd now the police! Come on, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.86,1:21:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你好 - 恭喜\N- Hello. - Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.90,1:21:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢 我们该干一杯 来吧\NThank you. We should have a toast. Right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.60,1:21:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,敬你的专辑?\NTo your album?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.67,1:21:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,是我们的专辑\NTo our album.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.19,1:21:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,是么?\NReally?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.88,1:21:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,不要高兴得太早 我只是尝试着戒\NDon't get too excited. I'm just trying it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.06,1:21:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,所以要用这个干么?\NShould we toast to that?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.98,1:21:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么有人会喝这玩意儿?\NGod damn. How do people drink that?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.90,1:21:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我们来玩个游戏\NWe're going to play a game.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.89,1:22:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我来放一首一定会让人想跳舞的歌\NI'm going to play a song that is impossible to not dance to.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.88,1:22:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,看看有谁能听着这歌忍住不跳舞\NI defy you not to dance to this song.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.02,1:22:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,听起来不错啊\NThis is good.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.02,1:22:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你想跳!我知道你想跳!\NYou know you want to! You know you want to!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.91,1:22:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你想!你很想跳吧!\NOh, you know you want to! You do!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.94,1:22:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧!来吧!\NOh! There it is! There it is!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.89,1:23:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我要送他们回家\NI'm gonna give them a ride home.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.38,1:23:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- 晚安 - 晚安\N- Good night. - Good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.88,1:23:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你做的一切\NThank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.02,1:23:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不谢谢你做的一切。\NNo, thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.85,1:24:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 混蛋 找个地方见面吧\NOK asshole, let's meet.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.27,1:24:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,巡演怎么样?\NSo how was touring?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.48,1:24:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,巡演很赞 很累 也很煎熬\NTouring was amazing. Grueling. Punishing.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.10,1:24:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,但又鼓舞人心\NInspiring.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.59,1:24:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- 在巡演里找到自己了么? - 我不知道\N- Did you find yourself? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.94,1:24:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,看来你找到了个大胡子\NWell, you certainly found a beard anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.81,1:24:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,看看\NLook at that thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.08,1:24:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是有点夸张 - 真的好多\N- It's intense. - It's big.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.11,1:24:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mim跟你一起巡演了吗?\NDid Mim go with you? On tour?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.65,1:24:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 所以 你想直接就谈这个么? - 是啊 - 好吧\N- You just wanna go straight into this then? - Yeah. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.47,1:24:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你们现在过得很幸福吗?还是你...\NAre you the happiest couple ever? Or did you...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.14,1:24:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一个月后分手了 她上车回到了纽约\Nbreak up after a month and she came back to New York on a bus.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.10,1:24:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,其实是火车\NIt was a train actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.72,1:24:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,对不起 我有点太贱了\NI'm sorry. I'm being a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.26,1:24:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,不会\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.39,1:25:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,确实是这样\NYou're entitled.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.97,1:25:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,那你呢 你最近在做什么?\NSo, what've you been up to?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.51,1:25:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}坚持\NHold on{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.57,1:25:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}坚持下去 这并不是我想要的\NHold on. Hold they're not for me{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.57,1:25:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,天 这简直太棒了 Gretta\NGod. It's amazing, Gretta.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.33,1:25:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真的吗? - 真的 背景音 还有这个城市\N- Really? - Totally. Ambient sound. The city.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.79,1:25:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- 就是只有这样了是吧?没有后期修声?什么都没有? - 不 不 不会了 就你听到的这样\N- And that's it? No over-dubs? Nothing? - No, no, no. It's just the way you hear it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.13,1:25:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,真的很棒\NGod, it's so great.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.65,1:25:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他们有跟你签合同么?\NAnd they're really offering you a deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.34,1:25:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,没有...我不知道 他必须先给他的合伙人听听看 然后再看情况吧\NNo...Well, I don't know. He has to play it to his partner first. So, we'll see.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.83,1:25:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我真不敢相信他对你的歌做了些什么\NI can not believe what he's done with your songs.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.34,1:25:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我也觉得他太棒了\NI know. He's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.73,1:25:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你应该让他帮你做专辑\NYou should get him to do your record.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.67,1:25:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,不行了 太晚了\NAh, it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.02,1:25:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,已经刚刚在洛杉矶完成了在做后期制作了\NI just finished mastering the record in LA.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.40,1:25:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我们沿途录制过来的\NYeah, I recorded in various studios on the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.47,1:25:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,哇 那么 专辑名是什么?\NWow. So what's it called?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.37,1:25:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,"在路上"\N"On the Road"
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.06,1:26:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 这就像杰克 凯鲁亚克的书一样\NSo it's kind of like Kerouac.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.98,1:26:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.31,1:26:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是的 没错 实在是无聊得可怕的专辑名 - 不会\N- Yeah it is. That's actually a terrible album name. - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.69,1:26:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说 对他来说就还行\NI mean. It worked for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.20,1:26:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,总之就是差劲\NNo. It's bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.18,1:26:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道你觉得这很无聊\NI know that you now it's bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.31,1:26:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,没有 我...\NNo. I'm...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.37,1:26:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你想听听吗?\NWould you like to go hear it?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.48,1:26:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我很乐意听 - 好的\N- I would love to hear it. - OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.68,1:26:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}若夜空中星辰不再相互凝望闪烁\NBut are we all lost stars{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.65,1:26:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}将如何继续照亮黑暗\Ntrying to light up the dark?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.53,1:26:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想我是看见你哭了\NAnd I thought I saw you out there crying{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.70,1:26:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想我听到了你呼唤着我的名字\Nand I thought I heard you call my name{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.67,1:26:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想我是看见你哭了\Nand I thought i heard you out there crying{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.69,1:26:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}还是一成不变\Njust the same{\i}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.55,1:26:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,好了 你有什么感想?\NAll right. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.60,1:26:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我需要再听一次\NI think I need to listen to it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.90,1:27:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不 我想要你对这首歌的第一印象\NNo, no. I want your immediate reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.09,1:27:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,第一印象?\NMy immediate reaction?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.95,1:27:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.43,1:27:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得这首歌好像失魂了 你知道吗?\NI think that you've lost the songs in the production, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.97,1:27:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像这歌名"Lost Stars"\NI mean. Okay, takes "Lost Stars".
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.95,1:27:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我写的是一首民谣\NI wrote it as a ballad.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.53,1:27:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,现在 这听起来像一首流行歌曲\NAnd it sounds like a piece of stadium pop.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.39,1:27:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊 但是 我想让这首歌成为热门单曲\NYeah but, I wanted to turn it into a hit.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.95,1:27:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- 为什么? - 什么为什么呢?这是什么问题呢?\N- Why? - Why? What kind of question is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.38,1:27:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,你是作者 你的名字将被记录在歌曲作家中 Gretta\NYou're the writer. You get sole writing credit on it, Gretta.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.49,1:27:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这对你来说是一个很好的机会\NThis is huge for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.55,1:27:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 但这样这首歌就失去了它的本意 这首歌很微妙的\NYeah,bI mean, but you weren't supposed to lose the song in it. It's delicate.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.53,1:27:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我真的觉得你应该重录 - 是啊 但是 大家都喜欢这样的 他们觉得很棒\N- I really think you should get it remixed. - Yeah, but everyone loves it when we do it. It's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.99,1:27:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你必须看看他们现场的反应 房间里的气氛都变了\NYou have to come see it live. The reaction to it. The energy in the room just changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.65,1:27:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你这么在意别人的想法?\NWhy are you so worried about what other people think?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.67,1:27:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们的歌\NIt's our song.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.10,1:27:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 但是音乐的存在不就是为了与他人分享么\NIt is, but isn't that what music is about? Sharing it with people.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.70,1:27:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不能是这首歌 Dave\NNo, not that song, Dave.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.46,1:27:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 所以那这是要代入谁?\NOkay. Well, good. Then who do we get to remix this?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.08,1:27:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mim 也许你应该把Mim代入进去\NMim. Maybe you should get Mim to remix it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.95,1:28:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- 真的吗?这明显跟专辑很没有关系 - 你这么觉得?\N- Really? So this is obviously not anything about the album. - You think?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.93,1:28:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你看 这就是做音乐的情侣总会发生的\NDon't become this music biz couple, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.11,1:28:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,争辩 关于我们的专辑\NArguing about our albums.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.53,1:28:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,但可笑的是\NThe funny thing about all this
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.62,1:28:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以把这张该死的专辑扔到海里去\Nis that I would throw that fucking record into the ocean
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.56,1:28:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们还可以继续现在的对话\Nif we could just continue this conversation right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.62,1:28:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,这也是我想表达的 好么?\NThis is what I want to talk about. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.93,1:28:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,而且如果我能以任何形式\NAnd if I could somehow say something or do anything
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.76,1:28:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,来弥补我做过的对不起我们的事\Nthat would undo what I did to us
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.90,1:28:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,请告诉我怎样做 拜托了\NJust tell me what it is. Help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.11,1:28:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你会做吗?\NWould you?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.83,1:28:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你会把它扔进大海吗?\NWould you throw it in the ocean?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.43,1:28:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你希望我这么做么?\NWould you want me to?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.13,1:28:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,算了\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.49,1:28:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得...我觉得一切都变了\NNo, I think...I think everything's changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.93,1:29:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我只是觉得很难再调整回来 - 我知道\N- And I'm just finding it a big hard to adjust. - I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.13,1:29:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这说得通 但我们会找到一个方法来\NIt makes sense. But we're just gonna have to find a way to
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.30,1:29:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,解决这个问题 一起\Nget through this. Get through this together.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.43,1:29:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么时候开始有这样的觉悟的?\NWhen did you realize that?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.76,1:29:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,当我听到你唱的到语音邮件\NWhen you sang to me on my voicemail.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.21,1:29:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我意识到 在这个地球上没有人\NAnd I realized that nobody on Earth in their right mind
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.11,1:29:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,能像你一样远程控制我的感情\Nwould ever do anything remotely like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.00,1:29:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,太让我难受 它折磨着我\NAnd that killed me. That crushed me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.02,1:29:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你彻底征服我了\NYou completely won me over.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.76,1:29:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,但这并不是我本意 我不想再让你回来的\NYou know I wasn't actually trying to win you over.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.11,1:29:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是想告诉你滚\NI was trying to tell you to fuck off.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.07,1:29:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我也已经说过了\NAnd I had.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.64,1:29:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,然后现在你又回来\NAnd now, you've come back and...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.84,1:29:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你开始回忆这一切\Nand you've opened the whole thing up again.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.90,1:29:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,而且我觉得其实 我想我得走了\NAnd I think actually, I think I'm gonna have to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.89,1:29:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,拿着吧\NTake that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.03,1:29:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我要走了 这一切有点太...\NI'm gonna go 'cause it's all a bit much.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.32,1:29:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我明白你的感受\NI hear you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.95,1:29:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你慢慢调整 我哪都不会去的 - 什么?你要一直坐在这把椅子吗?\N- Take your time. I'm not going anywhere. - What? Are you gonna stay on the bench?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.71,1:29:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 我会留下来的 我要永远活在这把椅子上\NYes. I'm gonna stay.I'm gonna live on this bench.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.88,1:30:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,周六到Gramercy来吧 拜托了\NCome to The Gramercy. On Saturday. Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.91,1:30:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,听听这首歌\NJust hear the song.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.63,1:30:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望你能看到人们有多喜欢\NI want you to see how everyone's just falling in love
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.81,1:30:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,喜欢这首你所写的东西\Nwith what you created.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.11,1:30:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,那请不要以那种方式唱\NPlease don't play it like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.83,1:30:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.05,1:30:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,哇 看看你 这么优雅 这才是我女儿\NWell, look at you. A vision of pure class. There's my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.13,1:30:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不是吧 就是这张吗? - 是啊\N- No way. Is this it? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.12,1:30:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- 就是这样 - 是的 - 你看起来棒极了\N- There you are. - Yeah. - You look great.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.37,1:30:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我能拿去给我的小伙伴们看么?\NCan I keep this? Show all my friends?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.46,1:30:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是它存在的意义呀\NThat's what it's for, babe.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.03,1:30:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,看看你\NLook at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.11,1:30:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,太好笑了\NHilarious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.16,1:30:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,有什么好笑的?\NWhy is that hilarious?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.45,1:30:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,只是我竟然一直不知道你这么有才华 我竟然不知道\NI just had no idea you were that talented. I mean, I just didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.45,1:30:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你是一个真正的吉他手 说真的你很有天赋\NYou’re a real guitar player. You got some talent. Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.90,1:31:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,然后呢?你想要让我组个乐队?\NWhat? Do you want me to start a band now?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.19,1:31:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊!那就组乐队吧!\NYeah! Let's start a band!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.09,1:31:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,好啊 组乐队吧!\NLet's start a band！
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.21,1:31:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么不呢?我会帮你录歌 当你的制作人\NYeah, Why not? I'll record you. I'll produce you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.23,1:31:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我觉得这很不错啊 - 是吗? - 是啊\N- I like this idea. - Do you? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.48,1:31:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,你会支持么?\NYou all motivated now?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.14,1:31:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是啊 这就是一个家族企业 像杰克逊五兄弟一样 - 到了\N- It's a family business. It's like the Jackson Five. - There you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.14,1:31:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 穆里根一家 - 你进来吗?\N- The Mulligan Three. - You coming in?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.66,1:31:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不了 我还要把片子放给索尔听 看看能不能达成协议\NNo. I'm going to go play that for Saul and see if we can get a deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.83,1:31:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,祝你好运 记得告诉我情况\NGood luck. Let me know how it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.43,1:31:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我爱你\NI love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.13,1:31:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道\NI know you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.40,1:31:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧 对 就是这样 太漂亮了\NCome on. Yeah. So pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.49,1:31:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,再见!\NBye!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.62,1:31:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你们的到来\NThanks for coming in guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.11,1:32:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这确实很棒 是一张很伟大的专辑\NThis is fantastic. You've got a great record.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.12,1:32:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我第一次没用心听 但是我不想再错过了\NI missed it on the first listen. But I don't want to miss it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.12,1:32:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我们很高兴你喜欢它\NWe're very glad that you like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.87,1:32:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经联系了几个洛杉矶的工作室\NWell, I reached out to some of my studio connects in L.A.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.23,1:32:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我们觉得可以放到电影里\Nand I was thinking we could get the first track placed in a film.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.27,1:32:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,出部电影 这也是一种推销策略\NWrite a film. There's also pilot season right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.75,1:32:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗 老兄 但我们对这些不感兴趣\NYeah man, we're not interested in any of that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.89,1:32:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 那么\NOkay, so then
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.68,1:32:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,你想怎么样?我们这是在谈论什么?\NWhat are you interested in? What are we doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.72,1:32:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得首先Dan应该回来工作\NWell, I think Dan needs his job back.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.64,1:32:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,是的 当然 说什么呢? 用我的办公室吧 我不介意的\NYeah, sure. What? Take my office. I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.02,1:32:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我想知道该怎么处理这张专辑?\NOkay. I guess I want to know, how does this work?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.10,1:32:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我们发行了一张专辑 我们一张卖...\NWe put the album out. We sell it for...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.99,1:32:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,就说每张专辑十块钱吧\NLet's say an album costs ten dollars a unit.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.28,1:32:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,音乐人赚取一美元\NThe artist gets a dollar.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.49,1:32:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,就跟卖书是一样的\NIt's the same in publishing. It's a buck for a book.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.06,1:32:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我在用一种特殊的方式想这个问题\NOh, I'm just thinking for this specifically.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.67,1:32:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我要组织一下语言\NI have to get my head around it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.02,1:32:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们做了一张不花任何成本的这张专辑\NThe album doesn't have any overhead because we did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.07,1:32:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这样子分配的话...\NAnd then, distribution...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.11,1:33:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它不会在店外的任何地方出售 它将被放到网上\NIt's not gonna go in stores. It's gonna go online.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.85,1:33:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们将有什么?有了口碑?\NAnd publicity would be...What? Word of mouth?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.01,1:33:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,所以 我认为我不明白的是...\NSo, I think what I'm wondering is...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.72,1:33:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么拿走我剩余的九美元?\Nwhy do you get nine out of ten of my dollars?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.89,1:33:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Gretta 你真是一个聪明的姑娘\NGretta, you're a very smart young woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.21,1:33:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你也是一个很坚定的艺术家\NAnd you're a determined artist.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.32,1:33:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你有张这么好的专辑\NYou have a wonderful project here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.46,1:33:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,而且 你的身后也会有两个团队指导你 推动你向正确的方向走\NAnd with the right team behind you to push you and guide you to the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.46,1:33:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,或者再聘请几位厉害的制作人替你再录几首歌\NMaybe hire a hot-shot producer to remix a couple tracks.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.53,1:33:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这将给你漫长的职业生涯创造一个顶点\NYou could have a hit record and a very long career.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.41,1:33:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,但是你知道 最终一切都取决于你\NBut you know, ultimately that's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.23,1:33:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你完全控制住他们了 - 我知道\N- Ah, you had them. You wound him up. - I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.64,1:33:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,当你没那么用心时最终的目标却总会实现 这真是太有趣了\NIt's amazing when you're not actually that interested, you always win the hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.20,1:33:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,是嘛 对我来说 事情从来没有这样过\NYeah. That's never really worked out that well for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.97,1:33:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我倒经常这样\NI found it worked very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.43,1:33:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,你会拿下那份合同的 那混蛋肯定会给你提供合同的\NYou're gonna get a deal. That asshole is gonna give you a deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.88,1:33:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不过到时候你就得谦虚一点了 - 绝不 - 当然了\N- You might have to compromise a little bit. - Never. - Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.39,1:33:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们应该经常这样做 - 你是什么意思?\NHey, we should do a bunch of these. - What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.48,1:34:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你喜欢欧版不? - 我喜欢啊\N- Do you like the European Series? - I like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.37,1:34:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,巴黎磁带 布拉格会议\NThe Paris Tapes. The Prague Sessions.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.70,1:34:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,柏林录音\NThe Berlin Recordings.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.09,1:34:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以坐火车在欧洲旅行\NWe could go all over Europe by rail.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.40,1:34:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,带着全组的人去\NWe could take the whole gang
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.49,1:34:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Rachel Malcolm Steve\NRachel, Malcolm, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.46,1:34:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- 所以... - 所以...\N- So... - So...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.88,1:34:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧 我想只能过段时间再见啦\NOh look. I guess I'll see you in a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.15,1:34:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.50,1:35:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,来表演吧 你的名字已经在演出列表上了 拜托了 Dave
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.92,1:36:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\NThank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.09,1:36:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.07,1:36:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,换吉他\NGuitar change.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.87,1:36:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,下一首歌曲实际上是一个很棒的音乐人送我的礼物\NThis next song was actually given to me by an amazing songwriter
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.80,1:36:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,更重要的是 她一个很棒的女人\Nand an even more amazing woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.01,1:36:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,所以这是一个很特别的歌\NSo it's a very special song.
